title: Red Pepper & Parmesan Tilapia
directions: Place egg substitute in a shallow bowl. In another shallow bowl, combine the cheese, Italian seasoning, pepper flakes and pepper. Dip fillets in egg substitute, then cheese mixture.
Place in a 15-in. x 10-in. x 1-in. baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 425Â° for 10-15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Yield: 4 servings.
ingredients: 1/2 to 1 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes
